{"body": "It depends on what scope makes the most sense.\r\n\r\n1. An instance variable is scoped to the test namespace.\r\n2. RAILS_TEST is a global constant (don't we have enough of those already?)\r\n\r\nMy opinion is that (1) is better because it involves less shared state.\r\n\r\nNote: I would guess that many people don't know about using instance variables with rake -- so there has not been a healthy discussion of these pros/cons so far.\r\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/15247660", "created_at": "2013-03-21T16:04:34Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/9177#issuecomment-15247660", "updated_at": "2013-03-21T16:04:34Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 9177, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/bluemont", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/d1a1f1e2464b843300e0ff2524ce4468?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fdbb2d77bd76fe13757f45c509cc3b27b.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/received_events", "gravatar_id": "d1a1f1e2464b843300e0ff2524ce4468", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "bluemont", "type": "Organization", "id": 1750239, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237ec6abd3543c151009cd7"}, "id": 15247660, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/9177"}
